            "answer_text": "In Algeria and Tunisia, due to political choice, French is going to disappear and be replaced by either English or Chinese.In subsaharan countries, French is the vehicular language and allow people to understand each other. The linguistic diversity of Africa is far greater than in Europe. A lot of Africans speak 3,4,5 native languages, but French is a better choice to conduct administrative, education, business. As the population grows, the French users get more numerous. ",
